  "body": {
    "view": {
      "representation": "view",
      "value": "<div class=\"contentLayout2\"><style>[data-colorid=ycswv77yh6]{color:#1155cc} html[data-color-mode=dark] [data-colorid=ycswv77yh6]{color:#3377ee}[data-colorid=tdbgoo6zl7]{color:#3d90b3} html[data-color-mode=dark] [data-colorid=tdbgoo6zl7]{color:#4c9fc2}[data-colorid=qdt5mmhtnj]{color:#3d90b3} html[data-color-mode=dark] [data-colorid=qdt5mmhtnj]{color:#4c9fc2}[data-colorid=bwu20qh08g]{color:#333333} html[data-color-mode=dark] [data-colorid=bwu20qh08g]{color:#cccccc}[data-colorid=b0mm268czz]{color:#1155cc} html[data-color-mode=dark] [data-colorid=b0mm268czz]{color:#3377ee}[data-colorid=eus1czjajk]{color:#3d90b3} html[data-color-mode=dark] [data-colorid=eus1czjajk]{color:#4c9fc2}[data-colorid=c2m3mw808b]{color:#3d90b3} html[data-color-mode=dark] [data-colorid=c2m3mw808b]{color:#4c9fc2}[data-colorid=w14mhuw0qs]{color:#3d90b3} html[data-color-mode=dark] [data-colorid=w14mhuw0qs]{color:#4c9fc2}[data-colorid=ayrpy57ktw]{color:#1155cc} html[data-color-mode=dark] [data-colorid=ayrpy57ktw]{color:#3377ee}</style>\n<div class=\"columnLayout fixed-width\" data-layout=\"fixed-width\">\n<div class=\"cell normal\" data-type=\"normal\">\n<div class=\"innerCell\">\n<p><br /><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/542219129/LamaLayer_header.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330545876&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/542219129/LamaLayer_header.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330545876&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"542219230\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"LamaLayer_header.jpg\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"542219129\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"83cd0bb7-f8ba-4496-90fa-ff9eb2bbdf4c\" data-media-type=\"file\" /></span><br /><span class=\"legacy-color-text-default\">This node vertically stacks 2 materials, with the base being at the bottom of the stack, with the Top layer above it.</span></p><h4 id=\"LamaLayer-MaterialTop\"><span data-colorid=\"qdt5mmhtnj\">Material Top</span></h4><p><span class=\"legacy-color-text-default\">Material to be used as the top layer.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span> <span class=\"legacy-color-text-default\">If no top layer is set, then the base material will be used by itself.</span></p><h4 id=\"LamaLayer-MaterialBase\"><span data-colorid=\"c2m3mw808b\">Material Base</span></h4><p><span class=\"legacy-color-text-default\">Material to be used as the base layer&nbsp;</span></p><h4 id=\"LamaLayer-TopMix\"><span data-colorid=\"eus1czjajk\">Top Mix</span></h4><p><span class=\"legacy-color-text-default\">Defines the mix between the base and top layers.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span> <span class=\"legacy-color-text-default\">This value can either be set via the slider or B/W map, PxrPattern, or float value.</span></p><h4 id=\"LamaLayer-TopThickness\"><span data-colorid=\"tdbgoo6zl7\">Top Thickness</span></h4><p><span class=\"legacy-color-text-default\">This value defines the thickness of the top layer.&nbsp;</span> <span class=\"legacy-color-text-default\">This value can either be set via the slider or B/W map, PxrPattern, or float value.</span></p><p><span class=\"legacy-color-text-default\">It is only relevant for interior effects associated with the top material, such as absorption. If the top material is itself a layer node, this value is passed on to its base component. And if the top material is a mix or add, this value is passed on to both child materials.</span></p><h4 id=\"LamaLayer-LayerMode\"><span data-colorid=\"w14mhuw0qs\">Layer Mode</span></h4><p>Switches the layering model.</p><ul><li><p><strong>Fresnel Blend</strong> simply attenuates the base layer using the transmission of the top layer.</p></li><li><p> <strong>Smooth Coating</strong> extends this model by also refracting the rays through the top layer.</p></li><li><p> <strong>Rough Coating</strong> extends the Smooth Coating model by clamping the roughness of the base layer to the roughness of the top layer.</p></li><li><p> <strong>Auto</strong> chooses the model depending on the materials that are being layered.</p></li></ul><p><span class=\"legacy-color-text-default\">In Auto mode, Fresnel Blend will be used when the base layer is diffuse, while Rough Coating will be used when the base layer is specular.</span></p><h1 id=\"LamaLayer-LayeringModes\">Layering Modes</h1><h2 id=\"LamaLayer-FresnelBlend\">Fresnel Blend</h2></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"columnLayout two-left-sidebar\" data-layout=\"two-left-sidebar\">\n<div class=\"cell aside\" data-type=\"aside\">\n<div class=\"innerCell\">\n<span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" alt=\"fresnel_blend_figure.png\" width=\"200\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/542219129/fresnel_blend_figure.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330544209&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=200&amp;height=167\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/542219129/fresnel_blend_figure.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330544209&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"233\" data-width=\"279\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"542219146\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"fresnel_blend_figure.png\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/png\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"542219129\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"aab8017b-e7d6-4417-ac76-980ab9cbff01\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/542219129/fresnel_blend_figure.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330544209&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=279&amp;height=233 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/542219129/fresnel_blend_figure.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330544209&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=200&amp;height=167 1x\" /></span></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"cell normal\" data-type=\"normal\">\n<div class=\"innerCell\">\n<p>The fresnel blend layer mode performs a weighted addition of the two materials, with the base material being weighted by the top materials transmission. This ensures that energy is conserved.</p><p>This is the simplest layer mode and is very commonly used in material models.&nbsp;It matches the behaviour of the MaterialX layer node.</p></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"columnLayout fixed-width\" data-layout=\"fixed-width\">\n<div class=\"cell normal\" data-type=\"normal\">\n<div class=\"innerCell\">\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table data-table-width=\"1800\" data-layout=\"align-start\" data-local-id=\"599f52b2-722f-4d86-8eb4-c8fcc88702fc\" class=\"confluenceTable\"><tbody><tr><td class=\"confluenceTd\"><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-left-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-left\" width=\"281\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/542219129/LamaShaderBall_fb_1.0.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330545166&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=281&amp;height=281\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/542219129/LamaShaderBall_fb_1.0.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330545166&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"512\" data-width=\"512\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"5422191